                    <span>I,as a university student with great interest to HTTP,borrow this book from school library. This book gives me basic and clear concept about http operations between client and server and stuff behind the scene. a list of explanation of http message and header is heleful too. later, the author writes very detail about proxy server,caching server and how the webserver are build for serious commercial use.<BR>I am able to finish 2/3 of this book in 3 days. it's so interesting and keeps me reading on.<P>This is definitely a book to get you start with all kind of term for HTTP and a grasp for HTTP/Webserver concept.<P>for ppl with solid backgroud on HTTP, i would recommend the "HTTP: The Definitive Guide".</span>
                  
